member.name: T:Ranorex.Plugin.Mobile.Tools.Android.Instrumentation.SmaliRedist
member.summary:
Ranorex code added to already existing smali dex packages could make them exceed the method count limit of the package. if that happens all the customer code in N dex packages need to be redistributed to N+1 packages to leave room for additions from Ranorex.
This could only done as a heuristic since we do not know in advance how much code is added where and how much registers and methods are affected. to pre-calculate that we need to have a real smali AST parser in place plus a lot of implementation effort.
current solution tries to hit a 20% (default) redistribution target by only moving root namespace folders. redistribution can be activated by -smali_redist or -smali_redist=percentage advanced instrumentation flag
Note: this is a minimal implementation which only creates a single new dex package. since e.g. 20% from each existing package is moved this approach does break if more them 5 packages already exist but choosing a to low value could have no effect.
Related Bug: 27942

member.name: M:Ranorex.Plugin.Mobile.Tools.Ios.Instrumentation.EntitlementsDerEncoder.GetEntitlementsDer(System.Collections.Generic.Dictionary{System.String,System.Object})
member.summary:
Below there are simple methods to prepare entitlements DER binary block, basing on entitlements file. This simplistic implementation does support only one dictionary, keys, strings, arrays and false/true values. Basing on sample entitlements found on Internet it should be sufficient. The implementation is missing such types as: int, date, time, data, null, real, other dictionaries. This implementation is done basing on reverse engineering, I could not find any sources and other information on Internet. I used many Stream buffers for each method, which is not best programmatic solution and there is a lot of place to improve it. However, it was the best and fastest algorithm to use.
Information about supported values is also here: https://opensource.apple.com/source/Security/Security-59754.140.13/OSX/utilities/der_plist.c.auto.html

member.name: T:Ranorex.Plugin.Mobile.Utils.EventSet
member.summary: Helper class to give some lightweight mechanics to work with sets of events. A event set is a number of events that have to be registered, and un-registered at once. We especially need this when we do asynchronous programming where sets of events are un-registered and registered multiple times. This class should help to define such an set at a single code location and not spread add/remove calls trough the whole code file.
member.remarks: This class should only be used if event sets are used that require exact add/remove mechanics, not for simple control events. Samples for such sets are MVP-presenter events or events for asynchronous programming.
